## {{!linkable_header('Course learning objectives')}}

In this course you will discuss, analyze, and evaluate a variety of algorithms.
You will learn standard computer science notation and evaluation techniques to classify the algorithm's resource requirements (processor time and/or memory).
Lastly, you will evaluate the algorithm's resource requirements as the amount of data increases.
The evaluation will
determine the asymptotic growth of resources of different algorithms,
compare and contrast alternative algorithms, and
justify the choice of an algorithm for a given purpose.

Modular learning objectives:
