## {{!linkable_header('Course Assignments')}}

### {{!linkable_header('Worksheets')}}

Worksheets are a way to reward coming to class and coming to class prepared.
Many worksheets will be done in breakout groups.
For any worksheet submitted on-time, scores of 75% or better will receive a score of 100%.
For any worksheet submitted before the grader is run, the minimum grade is 50%.

Since these are in-class worksheets, handing them in on time does require attendance.
Late assignments will be penalized 2% of the maximum score per hour or portion of an hour that they are late.
The minimum grade for worksheets submitted is 50%.
The grader will be run $\approx 1$ day after the worksheet is due.
Once the grader is run and answers are generally available, no late submissions will be accepted.

As this is a computer grading system, it is somewhat difficult to _unsubmit_ a worksheet or any assignment.
You will be given grace on any two assignments that you want to resubmit.
But you should consider that only the first submission of a homework or any assignment will be graded.

Lastly, there are [worksheet bonuses](#worksheet-bonus) and
the value of worksheets makes the final grade go to 102% (see [grading criteria](#grading-criteria)).
Therefore I hope you see worksheets as a low-stakes bonus for coming to class prepared.

