#### {{!linkable_header('Midterm boost')}}

In an effort to reward improvement, 
if the score increases from the first midterm to the second, 
a boost of 25% of the difference will be added to your first midterm score.
A similar boost of 25% of the difference between the second midterm and the final exam
will be added to your second midterm score.

For example, if you score 70% on the first midterm and 90% on the second midterm,
25% of the 20 point difference will be added to your first midterm score; 
your first midterm score increase by 5 points.
The boost will be reflected on the [grades page]({{get_url('grades')}}).

